The paper also involves analyzing the time complexity of the algorithm, which is a problem in theoretical computer science, and hence cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another likely sub-category. The algorithm involves maintaining the width of the point set as points are inserted or deleted, which is a problem in optimization, and hence cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves designing an efficient algorithm for a specific problem, which is a problem in computational complexity, and hence cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible sub-category.
